Project Setup and Usage Instructions

Installation

Clone the repository to your local machine:

git clone <repository-url>
cd <repository-folder>

Install the project dependencies:

npm install

Configuration

Create a .env file in the root directory of the project.

Use the .env.sample file as a template. Copy the contents of .env.sample to .env and replace the placeholder values with your own configuration details.

cp .env.sample .env

Update the .env file with your specific values. For example:

EMAIL='YOUR EMAIL'
PASSWORD='YOUR PASSWORD'

Running the Bot

Start the bot by running the following command:

npm start

The bot should now be running and ready to use!
